From 66139a48cee1530c91f37c145384b4ee7043f0b7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2014 18:02:55 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: usb-audio: Don't resubmit pending URBs at MIDI error recovery
Git-commit: 66139a48cee1530c91f37c145384b4ee7043f0b7
Patch-mainline: to be in 3.19-rc1

In snd_usbmidi_error_timer(), the driver tries to resubmit MIDI input
URBs to reactivate the MIDI stream, but this causes the error when
some of URBs are still pending like:

 WARNING: CPU: 0 PID: 0 at ../drivers/usb/core/urb.c:339 usb_submit_urb+0x5f/0x70()
 URB ef705c40 submitted while active
 CPU: 0 PID: 0 Comm: swapper/0 Not tainted 3.16.6-2-desktop #1
